---

## Core Class Features

### Hit Points
- **Hit Dice:** 1d8 per monk level  
- **Hit Points at 1st Level:** 8 + your Constitution modifier  
- **Hit Points at Higher Levels:** 1d8 (or 5) + your Constitution modifier per monk level  

---

### Proficiencies
- **Armor:** None  
- **Weapons:** Simple weapons, shortswords  
- **Tools:** Choose one type of artisan’s tools or one musical instrument  
- **Saving Throws:** Strength, Dexterity  
- **Skills:** Choose two from Acrobatics, Athletics, History, Insight, Religion, Stealth  

---

## Core Feature (Level 1)
> **Design Intent:** Establish the monk’s core combat loop using mobility and unarmed combat.

### Unarmored Defense
While you are wearing no armor and not wielding a shield, your AC equals  
**10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Wisdom modifier.**

### Martial Arts
You gain the following benefits while unarmed or wielding only monk weapons:
- You can use Dexterity instead of Strength for attack and damage rolls
- You use a Martial Arts die for unarmed strike damage
- When you take the Attack action, you can make one unarmed strike as a bonus action

**Scaling Guidance:**  
- Martial Arts die increases at levels 5, 11, and 17  
- Bonus action attack defines early-game power budget

---

## Modular Feature System
Starting at 2nd level, you gain access to **Ki**, a pool of spiritual energy used to fuel special abilities.

- **Ki Points:** Equal to your monk level  
- **Recovery:** All Ki points are regained after a short or long rest

### Ki Options
- **Flurry of Blows** — Spend 1 Ki to make two unarmed strikes as a bonus action after taking the Attack action.
- **Patient Defense** — Spend 1 Ki to take the Dodge action as a bonus action.
- **Step of the Wind** — Spend 1 Ki to take the Disengage or Dash action as a bonus action and double your jump distance until end of turn.

> **Balance Target:** Comparable to Battlemaster maneuvers or low-level spell slots

---

## Subclass System

### Monastic Tradition (Level 3)
You choose a monastic tradition, which grants features at levels:
- 3rd
- 6th
- 11th
- 17th

Each tradition defines a **combat axis** such as control, mobility, or burst damage.

---

## Ability Score Improvement (Levels 4, 8, 12, 16, 19)
+2 to one ability score or +1 to two.

---

## Level 5 Power Spike: Extra Attack, Stunning Strike

### Extra Attack
You can attack twice whenever you take the Attack action.

### Stunning Strike
When you hit with a melee weapon attack, you can spend 1 Ki point to attempt to stun the target. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of your next turn.

---

## Level-by-Level Features (5–20)

### Ki-Empowered Strikes (Level 6)
Your unarmed strikes count as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage.

### Evasion (Level 7)
When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage on a success and half damage on a failure.

### Stillness of Mind (Level 7)
You can use your action to end one effect on yourself that is causing you to be charmed or frightened.

### Unarmored Movement Improvement (Level 9)
Your speed from Unarmored Movement increases (e.g. +10 feet at 6th level, further increases at 10th, 14th, and 18th per your table). *Design: mobility scaling keeps the monk’s skirmish identity.*

### Purity of Body (Level 10)
You are immune to disease.

### Tongue of the Sun and Moon (Level 13)
You can understand and be understood by any creature that can understand a language.

### Diamond Soul (Level 14)
You gain proficiency in all saving throws. When you fail a saving throw, you can spend 1 Ki point to reroll it and must use the new result.

### Timeless Body (Level 15)
You suffer none of the frailty of old age, and you cannot be aged magically. You still need food and water.

### Empty Body (Level 18)
As an action, you can spend 4 Ki points to become invisible for 1 minute and gain resistance to all damage except force. You can end the effect early as a bonus action.

---

## Capstone: Perfect Self (Level 20)
When you roll initiative and have no Ki points remaining, you regain **4 Ki points**.

> **Design Intent:** Ensure the monk always begins an encounter functional.  
**Balance:** Reliable but not explosive; prevents “dead turn” scenarios with no infinite loops.
